# Elektron Build Engine — Cursor rules

Before doing anything in this repository, read and follow, in order:

1. `docs/ENGINEERING_CONSTITUTION.md`
2. `docs/AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md`
3. `docs/specifications/Revision_07.md` (ACTIVE_SPECIFICATION)
4. The current roadmap named in `docs/status/CURRENT_PHASE.md`
5. `AGENTS.md` (cross-agent rules, including the handoff protocol)

## Non-negotiables

- Never invent engineering values.
- Never delete evidence (raw research archives, handoff logs, registers).
- Never bypass guardrails, state machines, or configuration locks.
- Unknown data → file an OpenDataRequirement in
  `docs/research/OpenResearchRegister.md`; do not guess.
- No production code and no M10 work during the Revision 07 source
  ingestion phase.
- Propose README baseline updates; never rewrite the README silently.

## Handoff protocol (same format as Claude Code — no deviations)

- Before stopping, nearing practical usage/context limits, switching
  agents, or completing a milestone: update
  `docs/handoffs/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md` using
  `docs/handoffs/templates/HANDOFF_TEMPLATE.md`, append the superseded
  handoff to `docs/handoffs/HANDOFF_LOG.md`, and commit all valid work.
- Operational fallback — a handoff is ALSO mandatory after: every
  completed source-ingestion batch; every meaningful commit; every two
  hours of uninterrupted work; any unresolved contradiction recorded;
  any dirty working tree before switching agents.
- **Branch ownership (single-writer):** only one agent may own and
  modify an active branch at a time; the owner is the `Agent owner`
  field in `CURRENT_HANDOFF.md`. Do not edit until ownership is
  transferred to you (your name recorded, branch pushed, HEAD matching
  the recorded END_COMMIT). Before transferring away: commit or
  document uncommitted work, push, record END_COMMIT, set the new
  owner.
- Every handoff must include: branch, start commit, end commit, files
  changed, tests run, test results, blockers, next exact action, and
  forbidden actions.
- On receiving a handoff, BEFORE modifying any file: verify `git status`
  (clean tree, expected branch), verify HEAD against the handoff's end
  commit, read the active specification status, and run the claimed
  tests (or verify explicitly that no test suite exists).
- Never mark work complete based only on an agent's statement — record
  verification evidence in `docs/status/IMPLEMENTATION_LEDGER.md`.
